1
00:00:57,708 --> 00:01:02,135
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:02,625 --> 00:01:04,568
my day starts.

3
00:01:21,919 --> 00:01:26,252
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:26,708 --> 00:01:29,666
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:35,475 --> 00:01:37,484
Do I even have customers?

6
00:01:37,484 --> 00:01:39,400
More than you would expect.

7
00:01:41,836 --> 00:01:44,910
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

8
00:01:44,910 --> 00:01:49,527
FRIED CHICKEN WINGS

9
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:05,619
Fried chicken wings,

10
00:02:06,059 --> 00:02:07,767
are they popular recently?

11
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:12,923
I see them at restaurants around town,
so I tried my hand at them as well.

12
00:02:20,046 --> 00:02:22,046
-It's like eating crab.
-What?

13
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:27,653
Wings are good, but the bones...

14
00:02:27,653 --> 00:02:29,873
Yeah, they're difficult to eat.

15
00:02:29,873 --> 00:02:32,012
And your hands get so greasy.

16
00:02:32,012 --> 00:02:33,330
They ruin your lipstick, too.

17
00:02:33,727 --> 00:02:35,782
But they make us
feel like eating meat, right?

18
00:02:40,732 --> 00:02:44,440
I'm telling you, there are no good men
at parties in Nishi-Azabu.

19
00:02:45,208 --> 00:02:46,833
He said we'd get married

20
00:02:47,555 --> 00:02:50,455
at The Ritz-Carlton
and get a Harry Winston ring.

21
00:02:50,820 --> 00:02:52,528
To think he was cheating.

22
00:02:53,164 --> 00:02:56,185
He has money, right?

23
00:02:58,841 --> 00:03:00,674
I was his fourth girlfriend.

24
00:03:04,347 --> 00:03:06,497
There are no honest men among the rich.

25
00:03:06,904 --> 00:03:09,592
Accept that it was just a fantasy,
and move on.

26
00:03:10,010 --> 00:03:13,196
I'll be 26 next year.
I'm running out of time.

27
00:03:19,974 --> 00:03:23,474
That woman, the one
gobbling up the chicken wings...

28
00:03:24,283 --> 00:03:25,622
You mean Chizuru?

29
00:03:26,116 --> 00:03:28,389
She works at a club in Kabukicho, right?

30
00:03:28,965 --> 00:03:31,424
Recently, she's been coming after work.

31
00:03:31,765 --> 00:03:33,684
-That's her side job.
-What?

32
00:03:33,684 --> 00:03:35,224
She's a gravure model.

33
00:03:35,224 --> 00:03:37,738
I knew it! That's Chizuru Morino!

34
00:03:38,072 --> 00:03:39,850
Ten or so years ago,

35
00:03:39,850 --> 00:03:43,027
she would pop up here and there
in the magazines sometimes.

36
00:03:43,383 --> 00:03:44,983
So she's still at it.

37
00:03:45,634 --> 00:03:47,708
You shouldn't gossip.

38
00:03:47,991 --> 00:03:51,193
Especially as a regular.
No one will want to come here.

39
00:03:51,193 --> 00:03:53,087
-Right.
-You're one to talk.

40
00:03:53,307 --> 00:03:56,169
I'm saying it to myself, too.
Right, Master?

41
00:03:56,537 --> 00:03:59,604
Yeah. I'd be very grateful for that.

42
00:04:00,241 --> 00:04:01,857
He doesn't believe me!

43
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,116
Hello?

44
00:05:09,563 --> 00:05:10,480
Come in.

45
00:05:11,963 --> 00:05:14,399
-Excuse me.
-Hello.

46
00:05:14,658 --> 00:05:17,693
Miyako, about that
pachinko poster girl job...

47
00:05:17,693 --> 00:05:19,305
-Yes?
-You got it.

48
00:05:19,305 --> 00:05:20,192
Really?

49
00:05:20,192 --> 00:05:23,668
The CEO is crazy about you.

50
00:05:23,668 --> 00:05:25,668
-Do your best.
-Thank you very much.

51
00:05:26,574 --> 00:05:28,491
Any news about the audition?

52
00:05:29,949 --> 00:05:30,982
You didn't get it.

53
00:05:31,445 --> 00:05:34,054
I had something else for you.

54
00:05:34,054 --> 00:05:36,174
There are plans for a photobook.

55
00:05:36,634 --> 00:05:38,401
But there are conditions.

56
00:05:38,766 --> 00:05:40,741
I won't do nudes.

57
00:05:45,129 --> 00:05:47,420
Chizuru, what is it you want?

58
00:05:48,069 --> 00:05:51,100
You say you won't do this or that, but...

59
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,616
-You're 35 now?
-I'm 34.

60
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:54,749
Excuse me, I'm going home.

61
00:05:54,749 --> 00:05:56,499
-See you.
-Thank you for your work.

62
00:05:58,137 --> 00:05:59,741
Ah, Miyako!

63
00:06:00,140 --> 00:06:02,622
About your upcoming schedule...

64
00:06:07,613 --> 00:06:09,529
I'm running out of time, too.

65
00:06:11,764 --> 00:06:15,283
There's a party for rich CEOs in
Roppongi tomorrow. Wanna go?

66
00:06:15,283 --> 00:06:17,144
12,000 yen for two hours.

67
00:06:17,144 --> 00:06:20,144
No way. I'm short on money,
and I don't have the energy.

68
00:06:21,030 --> 00:06:23,697
You wouldn't pay, you would be paid.

69
00:06:29,488 --> 00:06:31,003
This is so good!

70
00:06:31,803 --> 00:06:34,077
You know Miyako?

71
00:06:34,077 --> 00:06:37,646
She got that job from a
CEO she met at a party.

72
00:06:37,646 --> 00:06:41,405
Just talk with them,
and it'll be over before you know it.

73
00:06:42,291 --> 00:06:44,416
Ah, nice to see you!

74
00:06:59,483 --> 00:07:01,150
Miss Chizuru Morino?

75
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:03,799
Yes?

76
00:07:05,733 --> 00:07:08,553
I bought all of the magazines you were in.

77
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:10,778
Your pictures at Shimoda beach...

78
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:13,583
They're amazing.

79
00:07:14,941 --> 00:07:16,275
Thank you.

80
00:07:17,650 --> 00:07:20,907
I haven't thought about Shimoda
for a long time.

81
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,266
Actually,

82
00:07:22,715 --> 00:07:24,763
I'm from Shizuoka.

83
00:07:25,983 --> 00:07:28,278
When I cycled past there from school,

84
00:07:28,941 --> 00:07:33,051
I'd think, "Chizuru Morino was here."

85
00:07:33,983 --> 00:07:35,372
Just thinking that...

86
00:07:36,275 --> 00:07:38,142
really excited me.

87
00:07:41,366 --> 00:07:42,616
Excuse me.

88
00:07:50,025 --> 00:07:54,400
The host is a friend from university.
I had no choice but to come.

89
00:07:55,851 --> 00:07:56,934
Is that so?

90
00:07:58,441 --> 00:08:02,191
I can't believe
I'm meeting Chizuru Morino.

91
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,440
Excuse my rudeness.
I mean, Miss Morino.

92
00:08:15,146 --> 00:08:18,405
THREE WEEKS LATER

93
00:08:21,129 --> 00:08:22,754
Is he the one we talked about?

94
00:08:23,423 --> 00:08:24,756
Toru Kanzaki.

95
00:08:25,315 --> 00:08:28,731
He's the head of an IT company
and said to be worth millions.

96
00:08:29,309 --> 00:08:32,991
I heard on TV that he was a big name
in the Internet society.

97
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:37,309
There're a lot of people
who say that about themselves.

98
00:08:37,577 --> 00:08:39,285
Here you go.

99
00:08:40,301 --> 00:08:44,051
Mr. Kanzaki said he absolutely had to try
the chicken wings here.

100
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,645
I see. I hope you like them.

101
00:08:57,824 --> 00:08:58,452
Delicious.

102
00:09:04,745 --> 00:09:06,260
Ah, are you having any?

103
00:09:06,672 --> 00:09:07,613
I'll have a salad.

104
00:09:08,261 --> 00:09:09,686
I have a shoot coming up.

105
00:09:11,924 --> 00:09:13,299
You're so professional.

106
00:09:14,181 --> 00:09:15,774
I'm impressed.

107
00:09:27,606 --> 00:09:28,940
It stands out, right?

108
00:09:29,546 --> 00:09:31,588
I haven't liked it since I was little.

109
00:09:33,283 --> 00:09:34,200
But...

110
00:09:35,326 --> 00:09:36,410
I'm keeping it.

111
00:09:37,101 --> 00:09:38,893
I want to be my natural self.

112
00:09:40,198 --> 00:09:43,110
This mole is proof of that.

113
00:09:46,558 --> 00:09:48,641
-"Your natural self"?
-Yes.

114
00:09:53,016 --> 00:09:56,641
A few years ago,
I wouldn't have been able to talk to you.

115
00:09:57,841 --> 00:09:59,091
But now, to be honest,

116
00:09:59,891 --> 00:10:01,558
I've gained some confidence.

117
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:05,136
Sorry.

118
00:10:12,415 --> 00:10:13,832
Thank you.

119
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,641
Excuse me.

120
00:10:23,387 --> 00:10:24,346
What's wrong?

121
00:10:25,282 --> 00:10:26,324
I see...

122
00:10:27,398 --> 00:10:29,315
Got it. I'm on my way.

123
00:10:31,136 --> 00:10:33,719
I'm sorry,
there's a problem at the office.

124
00:10:34,205 --> 00:10:36,801
-Is everything okay?
-Yes, it's nothing serious.

125
00:10:36,801 --> 00:10:38,516
The check, please.

126
00:10:41,962 --> 00:10:45,629
-Sorry, we only accept cash.
-What?

127
00:10:48,624 --> 00:10:50,832
In that case...

128
00:10:52,749 --> 00:10:53,999
Take this instead.

129
00:10:54,808 --> 00:10:57,433
Don't worry, Mr. Kanzaki.
I have cash. Please go ahead.

130
00:10:58,899 --> 00:11:00,024
I'm sorry.

131
00:11:08,719 --> 00:11:11,011
Master, five more chicken wings, please.

132
00:11:12,225 --> 00:11:13,933
I thought you were dieting, weren't you?

133
00:11:14,604 --> 00:11:17,354
Eating chicken wings isn't a good look.

134
00:11:18,356 --> 00:11:19,356
Okay, then.

135
00:11:22,172 --> 00:11:25,496
Those big-name IT CEOs
are a little strange, don't you think?

136
00:11:25,496 --> 00:11:29,080
You have to be
to survive the competition, I guess.

137
00:11:30,725 --> 00:11:33,809
I guess there are honest men
among the wealthy.

138
00:11:34,427 --> 00:11:36,594
Weren't you the one
who said there weren't?

139
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,526
I was wrong.

140
00:11:39,526 --> 00:11:42,372
Maybe my heart
had succumbed to bitterness.

141
00:11:51,279 --> 00:11:53,998
He's on his way to Sapporo now.

142
00:11:54,561 --> 00:11:56,961
Surely there aren't any flights this late.

143
00:11:57,808 --> 00:12:00,667
He's going by private jet.

144
00:12:04,299 --> 00:12:07,320
"I'll be done with work in the morning.

145
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:11,125
Why don't you take
tomorrow afternoon's flight to join me?

146
00:12:11,125 --> 00:12:13,278
I want you to come for my birthday."

147
00:12:13,278 --> 00:12:15,568
What? What should I do?

148
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,214
I can't go empty-handed!

149
00:12:17,214 --> 00:12:18,631
What should I get as a gift?

150
00:12:18,826 --> 00:12:19,631
Don't know.

151
00:12:19,631 --> 00:12:20,497
No idea.

152
00:12:20,497 --> 00:12:21,704
Me, neither.

153
00:12:23,276 --> 00:12:25,380
Really, what should I do?

154
00:12:26,414 --> 00:12:28,456
Shouldn't you be your natural self?

155
00:12:33,242 --> 00:12:34,075
Yes?

156
00:12:34,766 --> 00:12:38,371
Mr. Kanzaki, we've brought up the gift.

157
00:12:38,371 --> 00:12:39,454
May we come in?

158
00:12:40,016 --> 00:12:42,438
Sure. The door is open.

159
00:12:43,271 --> 00:12:44,271
Thank you.

160
00:12:57,580 --> 00:13:00,747
-Excuse us.
-Thanks.

161
00:13:19,687 --> 00:13:22,923
Happy birthday!

162
00:13:51,657 --> 00:13:53,073
I'm trying to be festive...

163
00:13:53,396 --> 00:13:54,687
Did I...

164
00:13:55,566 --> 00:13:57,024
go too far?

165
00:14:13,284 --> 00:14:15,576
I've never had anything like this before.

166
00:14:17,411 --> 00:14:18,578
You came...

167
00:14:20,542 --> 00:14:22,167
as your natural self.

168
00:15:02,503 --> 00:15:03,836
Honestly...

169
00:15:05,544 --> 00:15:07,335
my high school self...

170
00:15:09,901 --> 00:15:11,692
is crying in joy right now.

171
00:15:28,331 --> 00:15:29,539
Thank you.

172
00:15:37,447 --> 00:15:38,364
Here you go.

173
00:15:42,848 --> 00:15:44,639
You never leave any meat behind.

174
00:15:46,438 --> 00:15:48,105
I have four siblings,

175
00:15:48,539 --> 00:15:50,873
and we always fought over chicken wings.

176
00:15:52,206 --> 00:15:56,623
If we didn't eat all the meat off,
Mom yelled at us for wasting food.

177
00:15:57,268 --> 00:15:58,226
I see.

178
00:15:59,994 --> 00:16:02,328
But I won't eat them
when I'm with Mr. Kanzaki.

179
00:16:03,002 --> 00:16:05,377
I don't think you have to put on an act.

180
00:16:07,672 --> 00:16:09,256
I don't want him to dislike me.

181
00:16:13,970 --> 00:16:14,803
Hey...

182
00:16:15,738 --> 00:16:18,321
Do you have a measure?

183
00:16:18,926 --> 00:16:19,898
A measure?

184
00:16:21,531 --> 00:16:24,364
A measure for knowing how happy you are.

185
00:16:25,733 --> 00:16:28,123
I've never even thought about it before.

186
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:32,750
I don't have one.

187
00:16:33,966 --> 00:16:36,706
I've done my best as a model,

188
00:16:37,137 --> 00:16:40,096
but it's always been
others who decide my worth.

189
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:44,516
Since I met Mr. Kanzaki,

190
00:16:45,362 --> 00:16:48,484
I feel like I want to
become someone he could like.

191
00:16:49,111 --> 00:16:50,277
Are you okay with that?

192
00:16:51,927 --> 00:16:52,678
What?

193
00:16:53,101 --> 00:16:56,059
As long as you judge yourself
using someone else's measure,

194
00:16:56,764 --> 00:16:58,973
you'll never find your real self,

195
00:16:59,711 --> 00:17:01,044
no matter where you look.

196
00:17:14,085 --> 00:17:16,460
Three months passed after that.

197
00:17:17,152 --> 00:17:20,207
That CEO is amazing.

198
00:17:20,207 --> 00:17:22,332
It says the stock price has shot up again.

199
00:17:23,359 --> 00:17:26,500
Miss Chizuru,
are you quitting modeling?

200
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:27,292
What?

201
00:17:27,292 --> 00:17:30,398
I haven't seen your pictures lately,
and I'd love to see them again.

202
00:17:30,978 --> 00:17:32,682
Sorry to disappoint you.

203
00:17:32,682 --> 00:17:35,562
Chizuru is quitting
modeling soon.

204
00:17:35,562 --> 00:17:36,224
What?

205
00:17:36,224 --> 00:17:39,381
-Are you tying the knot with the CEO?
-No, not yet.

206
00:17:39,381 --> 00:17:42,554
But we've all been saying
it'll probably happen soon.

207
00:17:44,324 --> 00:17:47,283
He's been so busy,
he barely has time to talk.

208
00:17:47,924 --> 00:17:49,007
Actually...

209
00:17:49,627 --> 00:17:50,877
I'm a little worried.

210
00:17:53,798 --> 00:17:55,465
Good evening. Hi.

211
00:18:04,067 --> 00:18:04,907
Good evening.

212
00:18:06,361 --> 00:18:07,194
Please sit.

213
00:18:08,065 --> 00:18:11,690
That girl Yukari Tendo, she's been
in a bunch of commercials recently.

214
00:18:14,377 --> 00:18:15,752
Welcome.

215
00:18:16,393 --> 00:18:19,060
She said she wanted to have
some good chicken wings.

216
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,916
Could we start with five?

217
00:18:22,687 --> 00:18:23,687
Right away.

218
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:29,640
This kind of place is nice sometimes.
Don't you think, Miss Yukari?

219
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:30,565
Yes.

220
00:18:30,565 --> 00:18:34,444
Mr. Kanzaki,
you sure do know all kinds of places.

221
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:37,708
Chizuru, let's go.

222
00:18:40,106 --> 00:18:41,023
Your mole...

223
00:18:47,041 --> 00:18:48,468
Actually...

224
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,315
I've moved up to the next level.

225
00:18:52,881 --> 00:18:53,972
"The next"?

226
00:19:08,206 --> 00:19:10,123
I'm sorry for being so messy.

227
00:19:11,934 --> 00:19:13,517
Do you mind me being like this?

228
00:19:15,490 --> 00:19:18,282
I like you the way you are.

229
00:19:20,272 --> 00:19:21,189
But...

230
00:19:22,375 --> 00:19:25,278
two years ago,
I would've been too shy to talk to you.

231
00:19:26,419 --> 00:19:27,669
The truth is...

232
00:19:28,758 --> 00:19:32,050
I have a little more confidence now.

233
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:34,083
Excuse me.

234
00:19:36,867 --> 00:19:39,348
Look at him saying the word
"truth" many times.

235
00:19:39,850 --> 00:19:40,805
Hey, you!

236
00:19:41,453 --> 00:19:42,231
Yes?

237
00:19:43,031 --> 00:19:46,617
Don't you think you're being
insensitive to Chizuru?

238
00:19:47,218 --> 00:19:50,058
You shouldn't mess around
with people's feelings!

239
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:54,627
Mess around?

240
00:19:59,678 --> 00:20:00,928
I don't get it.

241
00:20:02,417 --> 00:20:04,792
If you see something better, you take it.

242
00:20:05,463 --> 00:20:07,629
I think that's normal.

243
00:20:08,352 --> 00:20:11,339
You did the same thing
when you met me, right?

244
00:20:17,342 --> 00:20:18,149
Yes.

245
00:20:18,557 --> 00:20:20,891
-Hold on, Chizuru!
-It's okay.

246
00:20:21,481 --> 00:20:25,148
I just gave him a present.

247
00:20:27,622 --> 00:20:29,789
Maybe I wasn't my natural self.

248
00:20:30,394 --> 00:20:32,352
I was just pretending to be.

249
00:20:36,593 --> 00:20:39,093
Thank you, Mr. Kanzaki.

250
00:20:41,161 --> 00:20:42,202
No, thank you.

251
00:20:42,736 --> 00:20:44,986
Even if it was just a temporary dream.

252
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:52,441
Master, I'm heading out.
Put it on one check.

253
00:21:01,406 --> 00:21:02,406
Here you are.

254
00:21:10,358 --> 00:21:12,858
I found my measure.

255
00:21:13,804 --> 00:21:14,804
I see.

256
00:21:16,416 --> 00:21:17,249
Let's go.

257
00:21:29,470 --> 00:21:30,720
Jeez!

258
00:21:31,905 --> 00:21:33,238
I'm sorry about that.

259
00:21:33,906 --> 00:21:35,531
Don't worry about it.

260
00:21:49,931 --> 00:21:51,181
I can't keep up.

261
00:21:56,120 --> 00:22:01,913
Soon after, Chizuru released
a nude photobook showing her pubic hair

262
00:22:01,913 --> 00:22:06,670
and quit her job as a model.

263
00:22:11,794 --> 00:22:13,166
MORINO GIFT WRAPPING CLASS

264
00:22:20,192 --> 00:22:22,610
You did all these yourself, Chizuru?

265
00:22:22,610 --> 00:22:26,652
I got certified in gift wrapping
and opened a class in Minami-Aoyama.

266
00:22:27,389 --> 00:22:28,972
I have a lot of students.

267
00:22:29,584 --> 00:22:31,381
What a change of scenery.

268
00:22:31,381 --> 00:22:34,088
But isn't the rent expensive?

269
00:22:34,088 --> 00:22:36,588
Yeah, I had to use all the money
from the photobook.

270
00:22:37,111 --> 00:22:38,403
Here you go.

271
00:22:38,723 --> 00:22:41,927
This! This is what I've been wanting!

272
00:22:41,927 --> 00:22:43,385
It's been a long time.

273
00:22:47,575 --> 00:22:51,783
Being your natural self
suits you much better, Chizuru.

274
00:22:52,072 --> 00:22:53,158
I agree.

275
00:22:53,567 --> 00:22:54,425
Right?

276
00:22:55,642 --> 00:22:56,767
I realized...

277
00:22:57,660 --> 00:23:00,342
there's something you can never wrap up.

278
00:23:01,075 --> 00:23:01,906
What's that?

279
00:23:04,269 --> 00:23:05,269
Yourself.

280
00:23:05,803 --> 00:23:07,547
You can't give that to others, right?

281
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:11,357
That's right.

282
00:23:22,836 --> 00:23:26,505
Making cuts in the front and back
of the wings with a knife...

283
00:23:26,505 --> 00:23:28,213
helps the flavors soak in better.

284
00:23:31,267 --> 00:23:32,892
Master, what are you looking at?

285
00:23:34,553 --> 00:23:36,178
Is that Chizuru's?

286
00:23:38,624 --> 00:23:40,124
Did you buy it yourself?

287
00:23:43,810 --> 00:23:45,310
Thanks for the food!

288
00:25:03,470 --> 00:25:08,476
THIS STORY IS A WORK OF FICTION

